| **NetFlow / IPFIX**   | `{{ netflow_index | default("netflow-*") }}`           | `src_ip`, `dst_ip`, `dst_port`, `protocol`   | `{{ log_retention | default("90 days") }}` |
| **Honeypot Events**   | `{{ honeypot_log_path | default("honeypot-events-*") }}`| `src_ip`, `dst_port`, `protocol`, `payload` | `{{ log_retention | default("90 days") }}` |
| **PCAP Evidence**     | `captures/portscan_{{ source_ip | default("*") }}_*.pcap` | Raw packets | `{{ log_retention | default("90 days") }}` |
| **SIEM Alerts**       | `{{ siem_index | default("siem-alerts-*") }}`          | `rule_id`, `severity`, `src_ip`              | `{{ log_retention | default("90 days") }}` |

### SIEM Detection Queries

**Query 1 – SYN Scan Rate Detection (primary trigger):**
```splunk
index=netflow-* src_ip="{{ source_ip | default("*") }}"
  flags="SYN" dest_subnet="{{ target_subnet | default("*") }}"
  | bin _time span=1m
  | stats dc(dest_port) as unique_ports, count as total_pkts by _time, src_ip
  | where unique_ports > {{ port_count_threshold | default(50) }}
  | eval scan_rate = unique_ports . " ports/min"
  | sort - unique_ports
```

**Query 2 – Sequential Port Pattern Detection:**
```splunk
index=firewall-logs src_ip="{{ source_ip | default("*") }}"
  | bin _time span=30s
  | stats values(dest_port) as ports, dc(dest_port) as port_count by _time, src_ip, dest_ip
  | where port_count > 10
  | eval sorted_ports = mvjoin(mvsort(ports), ",")
  | table _time, src_ip, dest_ip, port_count, sorted_ports
```

**Query 3 – Honeypot Hit Correlation:**
```splunk
index=honeypot-events src_ip="{{ source_ip | default("*") }}"
  | bin _time span=5m
  | stats count as honeypot_hits, values(dest_port) as bait_ports,
          dc(dest_port) as unique_bait_ports by _time, src_ip
  | sort - honeypot_hits
```

**Query 4 – IDS Scan Signature Alerts:**
```splunk
index=ids-alerts sig_category="SCAN" src_ip="{{ source_ip | default("*") }}"
  | stats count as alert_count, values(sig_name) as signatures by src_ip, dest_ip
  | sort - alert_count
```

**Query 5 – Cross-Segment Firewall Policy Violation:**
```splunk
index=firewall-logs src_zone!="{{ firewall_zone | default("*") }}"
  dest_ip="{{ target_subnet | default("*") }}" action="ALLOW"
  | where src_ip = "{{ source_ip | default("*") }}"
  | table _time, src_ip, src_zone, dest_ip, dest_zone, dest_port, action
  | sort - _time
```

